    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Empiric coverage for pneumonia due to aerobic gram-negative bacilli (e.g., Gram-negative bacilli seen on Gram stain)",
        "Risk factors: alcohol use disorder with necrotizing pneumonia, underlying chronic bronchiectasis (e.g., cystic fibrosis), chronic tracheostomy, mechanical ventilation, febrile neutropenia and pulmonary infiltrates, septic shock, underlying malignancy, or organ failure."
      ]
    },
